                        "content": "A client has a prescription for sucralfate, orally 4 times daily. The nurse writes which schedule for this medication on the medication administration record?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nSucralfate is prescribed to treat gastric ulcers. It would be scheduled for administration 1 hour before meals and at bedtime to allow it to form a protective coating over the gastric ulcer to prevent irritation by food, gastric acid, and mechanical movement of the stomach. The other options are incorrect.",
