                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nA client who chronically uses aspirin is prone to gastric mucosal injury, which causes epigastric pain as a symptom. Misoprostol is a gastric protectant specifically given to prevent this occurrence. Diarrhea can be a side effect of the medication, but it is not an intended effect. Bleeding and joint aches are not relieved by misoprostol.",
