                        "content": "The client with peptic ulcer disease is prescribed medication therapy. The nurse explains the medications to the client and explains that sucralfate will help to heal the ulcer by doing what?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nMedication therapy is used to treat peptic ulcer disease by three mechanisms: eradicating H. pylori (or other bacterial infections), reducing gastric acidity, and enhancing mucosal defenses. Sucralfate works by enhancing mucosal defenses. Antibiotics treat infection and eradicate H. pylori. Antisecretory agents, misoprostol, and antacids work by reducing gastric acidity.",
                        "id": "9f74cd3a03a14ed880509a954d16b19a",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "5897a68354e94296a97c244c27f7224b",
                                "content": "Take the sucralfate once a day at bedtime with food."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "0441a02d8e04412bb19b64d94d3a05ba",
                                "content": "Take the sucralfate daily with the proton pump inhibitor."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "bb27f2bb1f484ee8932ba10e532f22af",
                                "content": "Take the sucralfate before meals and at bedtime on an empty stomach."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "10948eca75644e7e8c8f8e8e68ce75ea",
                                "content": "Take the sucralfate immediately after eating and within 30 minutes of an antacid."
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
