                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nSucralfate is an antiulcer medication that promotes ulcer healing by creating a protective barrier against acid and pepsin. It should be taken on an empty stomach. The usual recommended adult dosage is 1 gram 4 times a day, taken 1 hour before meals and at bedtime. Options 1, 2, and 4 are incorrect, as sucralfate would be taken on an empty stomach, at least twice a day, and at least 30 minutes apart from an antacid.",
